- Game: [CORE]
- Developer: PBStriker101

- MAIN OBJECTIVE:
Build a small but functional game prototype with:
1) turn-based combat,
2) simple map movement,
3) minimal UI feedback,
4) basic character progression.

- PROJECT SCOPE:
Strict MVP. The goal is not flexibility or polish yet.
The goal is one complete playable loop.

- SUCCESS CONDITION:
The project counts as “working” when the player can:
1) start the game,
2) move through a small map,
3) enter a battle,
4) choose actions,
5) finish the battle correctly,
6) receive a progression reward or choice,
7) continue or end the run without the game breaking.

- COMPLEXITY LEVEL:
Minimal.

- DEVELOPMENT CYCLE:
As small as possible (2+ weeks)

--------------------------------------------------
CORE SYSTEMS
--------------------------------------------------

- Entity:
Represents a combat unit with stats, health, abilities, and active effects.

- Ability:
Represents an action a unit can perform in combat.

- Effect:
Represents a temporary modifier or condition that changes entity state over time.

- Action:
Represents a concrete combat decision made by an entity for a turn.

- TurnManager:
Builds, orders, and executes actions during battle.

- BattleContext:
Stores all combat data needed to run a battle correctly.

- MapManager:
Stores a very small map and its node connections.

- JourneyHandler:
Handles player movement between map nodes and event triggering.

- CharacterCreator:
Creates player and enemy entities for testing and gameplay.

--------------------------------------------------
MVP MILESTONES
--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 1: ENTITY FOUNDATION
Goal: Create a valid combat unit.

1) Create the Entity class with the minimum required state:
- name
- hp / max hp
- attack or damage-related stat
- speed
- alive/dead state
- list of abilities
- list of active effects

2) Prove that Entity state can be:
- read correctly
- modified correctly
- checked for alive/dead state

Completion check:
- Create at least 2 test entities. (COMPLETED)
- Modify their stats and HP. (COMPLETED)
- Confirm that death state is detected correctly. (COMPLETED)

--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 2: ABILITIES WORK
Goal: Make entities perform meaningful actions.

3) Define Ability with the minimum required information:
- name
- type or category
- power or effect strength
- cooldown or usage restriction if needed
- valid target type

4) Prove that Abilities are usable in isolation.

5) Add Abilities to Entities and prove that:
- entities can access their abilities
- abilities can affect targets correctly
- abilities can fail gracefully if invalid

Completion check:
- One entity can damage another using an ability. (COMPLETED)
- One invalid action case is safely handled. (MISSING)

--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 3: EFFECTS WORK
Goal: Add temporary state changes.

6) Define Effect as a temporary modifier with:
- name
- duration
- onTurnStart behavior if needed
- onTurnEnd behavior if needed
- stat modification or condition logic

7) Prove that effects can be:
- applied
- updated over turns
- removed when expired

Completion check:
- Apply one simple effect such as:
  - speed buff,
  - poison,
  - defense reduction,
  or similar. (COMPLETED)
- Confirm that duration decreases correctly. (COMPLETED)
- Confirm that expiration removes the effect. (COMPLETED)

--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 4: ACTIONS AND TURN ORDER
Goal: Represent and resolve combat choices correctly.

8) Define Action as the unit of combat intent with:
- actor
- target
- selected ability or action type
- priority
- speed snapshot
- tie breaker

9) Define TurnManager responsibilities clearly:
- collect actions
- order them
- transfer them into execution order
- execute them safely

10) Implement action ordering rules:
- priority first
- speed second
- tie breaker third

11) Prove that TurnManager can:
- collect multiple actions
- order them correctly
- execute them in the correct sequence

12) Verify that TurnManager can alter BattleContext safely.

Completion check:
- Run one test round with multiple entities.
- Confirm the exact action order matches expectations.
- Confirm that executed actions change combat state correctly.

--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 5: COMPLETE BATTLE LOOP
Goal: Make one full battle playable from start to finish.

13) Define BattleContext with the minimum required combat data:
- allies
- enemies
- battle state
- turn state
- victory / defeat state

14) Build the complete battle loop:
- battle starts
- entities choose actions
- actions are ordered
- actions execute
- effects tick
- dead units are removed from valid decision flow
- victory or defeat is detected
- battle ends cleanly

Completion check:
- A full battle can run from start to finish without manual fixes.
- At least one side wins correctly.
- No dead unit acts after death.

--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 6: MAP LOOP
Goal: Connect battle to progression through space.

15) Define a very small map structure:
- 3 to 5 nodes maximum
- simple connections
- one start node
- one battle node
- one reward or end node

16) Implement JourneyHandler to allow movement between connected nodes.

17) Trigger at least one battle from map travel.

Completion check:
- Player can move through the map.
- Entering the battle node starts combat.
- Winning returns control safely.

--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 7: BASIC PROGRESSION
Goal: Make victory lead to growth.

18) Add one simple progression reward after battle:
- gain HP
- gain stat point
- unlock one ability
- choose one of two upgrades

19) Prove that progression changes future battles.

Completion check:
- A post-battle reward is offered.
- The next battle or state reflects the reward correctly.

--------------------------------------------------

MILESTONE 8: MINIMUM PLAYABLE VERSION
Goal: Have something that can honestly be called a game.

20) Build the smallest possible playable flow:
- start
- move
- fight
- win or lose
- receive reward
- continue or end

21) Add minimal UI feedback:
- text output is enough
- player must be able to understand what happened

22) Freeze scope.
Do not add new systems until the full loop is stable.

Completion check:
- The game can be run and played from start to finish in one short session.

--------------------------------------------------
NON-GOALS FOR MVP
--------------------------------------------------

Do not prioritize these before the core loop works:
- advanced AI
- large map generation
- multiple classes/races
- inventory systems
- save/load
- complicated menus
- animation polish
- deep balancing
- content variety
- framework-level flexibility

--------------------------------------------------
PROGRESS CHECK RULE
--------------------------------------------------

A task only counts as finished if it is both:
1) implemented
and
2) proven through a test or complete flow.

If it exists in code but is not proven in the game loop, it is not done.


